dom-dommatrix-dommatrix.name: DOMMatrix
dom-dommatrix-dommatrix.summary: The DOMMatrix constructor creates a new DOMMatrix object which represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations.
dom-dommatrix-dommatrix.title: DOMMatrix: DOMMatrix() constructor

DOMMatrix.name: DOMMatrix
DOMMatrix.summary: The DOMMatrix interface represents 4×4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations including rotation and translation. It is a mutable version of the DOMMatrixReadOnly interface.
DOMMatrix.title: DOMMatrix (WebKitCSSMatrix)

DOMMatrix.name: DOMMatrixReadOnly
DOMMatrix.summary: The DOMMatrixReadOnly interface represents a read-only 4×4 matrix, suitable for 2D and 3D operations. The DOMMatrix interface — which is based upon DOMMatrixReadOnly—adds mutability, allowing you to alter the matrix after creating it.
DOMMatrix.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly

dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.name: DOMMatrixReadOnly
dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.summary: The DOMMatrixReadOnly constructor creates a new DOMMatrixReadOnly object which represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations.
dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly: DOMMatrixReadOnly() constructor

dom-dommatrixreadonly-flipx.name: flipX
dom-dommatrixreadonly-flipx.summary: The flipX() method of the DOMMatrixReadOnly interface creates a new matrix being the result of the original matrix flipped about the x-axis.
dom-dommatrixreadonly-flipx.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly: flipX() method

dom-dommatrixreadonly-scale.name: scale
dom-dommatrixreadonly-scale.summary: The scale() method of the DOMMatrixReadOnly interface creates a new matrix being the result of the original matrix with a scale transform applied.

firefox.notes: Firefox 69 introduced support for the modern six-parameter syntax for scale(). Previously, it only supported the older three-parameter syntax: scale(scaleX[, originX][, originY]]]).

firefox_android.notes: Firefox for Android 79 introduced support for the modern six-parameter syntax for scale(). Previously, it only supported the older three-parameter syntax: scale(scaleX[, originX][, originY]]]).

dom-dommatrixreadonly-scale.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly: scale() method

dom-dommatrixreadonly-translate.name: translate
dom-dommatrixreadonly-translate.summary: The translate() method of the DOMMatrixReadOnly interface creates a new matrix being the result of the original matrix with a translation applied.
dom-dommatrixreadonly-translate.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly: translate() method

dom-dompoint-dompoint.name: DOMPoint
dom-dompoint-dompoint.summary: The DOMPoint() constructor creates and returns a new DOMPoint object, given the values for some or all of its properties.
dom-dompoint-dompoint.title: DOMPoint: DOMPoint() constructor

dom-dompoint-frompoint.name: fromPoint_static
dom-dompoint-frompoint.summary: The DOMPoint static method fromPoint() creates and returns a new mutable DOMPoint object given a source point.
dom-dompoint-frompoint.title: DOMPoint: fromPoint() static method

dom-dompointreadonly-w.name: w
dom-dompointreadonly-w.summary: The DOMPoint interface's w property holds the point's perspective value, w, for a point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-w.title: DOMPoint: w property

dom-dompointreadonly-w.name: w
dom-dompointreadonly-w.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's w property holds the point's perspective value, w, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-w.title: DOMPointReadOnly: w property

dom-dompointreadonly-x.name: x
dom-dompointreadonly-x.summary: The DOMPoint interface's x property holds the horizontal coordinate, x, for a point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-x.title: DOMPoint: x property

dom-dompointreadonly-x.name: x
dom-dompointreadonly-x.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's x property holds the horizontal coordinate, x, for a read-only point in space. This property cannot be changed by JavaScript code in this read-only version of the DOMPoint object.
dom-dompointreadonly-x.title: DOMPointReadOnly: x property

dom-dompointreadonly-y.name: y
dom-dompointreadonly-y.summary: The DOMPoint interface's y property holds the vertical coordinate, y, for a point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-y.title: DOMPoint: y property

dom-dompointreadonly-y.name: y
dom-dompointreadonly-y.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's y property holds the vertical coordinate, y, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-y.title: DOMPointReadOnly: y property

dom-dompointreadonly-z.name: z
dom-dompointreadonly-z.summary: The DOMPoint interface's z property specifies the depth coordinate of a point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-z.title: DOMPoint: z property

dom-dompointreadonly-z.name: z
dom-dompointreadonly-z.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's z property holds the depth coordinate, z, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-z.title: DOMPointReadOnly: z property

DOMPoint.name: DOMPoint
DOMPoint.summary: A DOMPoint object represents a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system; it includes values for the coordinates in up to three dimensions, as well as an optional perspective value. DOMPoint is based on DOMPointReadOnly but allows its properties' values to be changed.
DOMPoint.title: DOMPoint

DOMPoint.name: DOMPointReadOnly
DOMPoint.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface specifies the coordinate and perspective fields used by DOMPoint to define a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system.
DOMPoint.title: DOMPointReadOnly

dom-dompointreadonly-dompointreadonly.name: DOMPointReadOnly
dom-dompointreadonly-dompointreadonly.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly() constructor returns a new DOMPointReadOnly object representing a point in 2D or 3D space, optionally with perspective, whose values cannot be altered by script code.
dom-dompointreadonly-dompointreadonly.title: DOMPointReadOnly: DOMPointReadOnly() constructor

dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.name: fromPoint_static
dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.summary: The static DOMPointReadOnly method fromPoint() creates and returns a new DOMPointReadOnly object given a source point.
dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.title: DOMPointReadOnly: fromPoint() static method

dom-dompointreadonly-tojson.name: toJSON
dom-dompointreadonly-tojson.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly method toJSON() returns an object giving the JSON form of the point object.
dom-dompointreadonly-tojson.title: DOMPointReadOnly: toJSON() method

DOMQuad.name: DOMQuad
DOMQuad.summary: A DOMQuad is a collection of four DOMPoints defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning DOMQuads lets getBoxQuads() return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy bounds attribute returning a DOMRectReadOnly for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.
DOMQuad.title: DOMQuad

dom-domrect-domrect.name: DOMRect
dom-domrect-domrect.summary: The DOMRect() constructor creates a new DOMRect object.
dom-domrect-domrect.title: DOMRect: DOMRect() constructor

DOMRect.name: DOMRect
DOMRect.summary: A DOMRect describes the size and position of a rectangle.
DOMRect.title: DOMRect

DOMRect.name: DOMRectReadOnly
DOMRect.summary: The DOMRectReadOnly interface specifies the standard properties used by DOMRect to define a rectangle whose properties are immutable.
DOMRect.title: DOMRectReadOnly

DOMRect.name: SVGRect
DOMRect.summary: The SVGRect represents a rectangle. Rectangles consist of an x and y coordinate pair identifying a minimum x value, a minimum y value, and a width and height, which are constrained to be non-negative.
DOMRect.title: SVGRect

dom-domrectreadonly-domrectreadonly.name: DOMRectReadOnly
dom-domrectreadonly-domrectreadonly.summary: The DOMRectReadOnly() constructor creates a new DOMRectReadOnly object.
dom-domrectreadonly-domrectreadonly.title: DOMRectReadOnly: DOMRectReadOnly() constructor

dom-domrectreadonly-bottom.name: bottom
dom-domrectreadonly-bottom.summary: The bottom read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the bottom coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as y + height, or y if height is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-bottom.title: DOMRectReadOnly: bottom property

dom-domrectreadonly-fromrect.name: fromRect_static
dom-domrectreadonly-fromrect.summary: The fromRect() static method of the DOMRectReadOnly object creates a new DOMRectReadOnly object with a given location and dimensions.
dom-domrectreadonly-fromrect.title: DOMRectReadOnly: fromRect() static method

dom-domrectreadonly-height.name: height
dom-domrectreadonly-height.summary: The height read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the height of the DOMRect.
dom-domrectreadonly-height.title: DOMRectReadOnly: height property

dom-domrectreadonly-left.name: left
dom-domrectreadonly-left.summary: The left read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the left coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as x, or x + width if width is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-left.title: DOMRectReadOnly: left property

dom-domrectreadonly-right.name: right
dom-domrectreadonly-right.summary: The right read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the right coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as x + width, or x if width is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-right.title: DOMRectReadOnly: right property

dom-domrectreadonly-top.name: top
dom-domrectreadonly-top.summary: The top read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the top coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as y, or y + height if height is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-top.title: DOMRectReadOnly: top property

dom-domrectreadonly-width.name: width
dom-domrectreadonly-width.summary: The width read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the width of the DOMRect.
dom-domrectreadonly-width.title: DOMRectReadOnly: width property

dom-domrectreadonly-x.name: x
dom-domrectreadonly-x.summary: The x read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the x coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.
dom-domrectreadonly-x.title: DOMRectReadOnly: x property

dom-domrectreadonly-y.name: y
dom-domrectreadonly-y.summary: The y read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the y coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.
dom-domrectreadonly-y.title: DOMRectReadOnly: y property
